# MCP consent (example)
#
# To allow MCP tools in this repository when not in a Task subagent session,
# create an empty file next to this one named exactly:
#
#   allow-mcp
#
# Example:
#   touch .cursor/allow-mcp
#
# Subagent sessions automatically create `.cursor/.subagent-active` via hooks
# so MCP may run during Task without this file. See `.cursor/hooks/mcp-gate.py`.
